The paper proposes an approach to statically check web API requests in JavaScript, which involves analyzing the code and checking whether the requests conform to given web API specifications. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also involves analyzing and verifying the correctness of the code, which could fall under the categories of software development (cs.SD) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the proposed approach could be integrated with code editors or continuous integration tools, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
